synopsis: We are introduced to our heroes at the country of Mugen's annual athletic meet, which commemorates the legendary race for a spot on the Zodiac that was held years ago. The race is interrupted, however, once the evil Jyarei Monsters reveal themselves to the world.
On the Eto Rangers' first mission, the Jyarei Monsters have warped the world of Momotaro into an interplanetary war.

Nothing seems to be wrong in the world of Cinderella, so the Eto Rangers use the opportunity to take a load off. While they're at it, Soufflé falls in love. Perhaps they'll all go dancing, but not in the way they expect...

title.jp: Silly Rabbit, Winning is for Tortoises

synopsis: It's race time! And behind the wheel of a top-notch racecar, the hare might actually stand a chance. Which is bad. To make matters worse, Pochiro and Monk are willing to put one-upping each other ahead of making sure the mission is completed!
Sick and tired of being treated like a clucking joke by her own teammates, Tart takes the Ugly Duckling, now an ostrich that can't swim, under her wing.

A little bout of roughhousing has left Bakumaru with a sprained wrist. And when going to a world corrupted into a Western shootout, that doesn't exactly leave him with a good firing hand. It's up to Monk to take the role of the Monkey King and handle things himself.

The story can't even start if the old couple never finds the child in the forest. And since they've suddenly found themselves with the most successful spaghetti restaurant to ever exist, they don't have any free time to do that. Cream, Tart, and Soufflé help to lighten the load while Gaoh, Hols, and Urii do a little babysitting.

title.jp: Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Riding Hood

synopsis: Little Red Riding Hood's learned to fight back against the Big Bad Wolf. Between Urii's newfound friendship with her and her desire for revenge, she has a difficult decision to make. In the meantime, Nyanma takes the next step in her master plan.

title.jp: We Can't Stop Here, This is Giant Country!

synopsis: Jack is a total airhead. Though whether that's a corruption or not is unclear. What IS corrupted is that the giant's castle is now a bustling city brimming with giants, and the Eto Rangers have to make sure Jack doesn't get himself crushed. And speaking of little things that can be crushed, Bakumaru deals with his hatred of spiders.

Pinocchio is now made of gold instead of wood. And he still has that nose growing curse. So, instead of it being a nuisance, now telling lies makes him richer. That's definitely not a metaphor for anything.

The Eto Rangers think they have it easy this time when they see the Jyarei Monster on its way to the novel world. But it turns out to be like finding a needle in a stack of other needles. There's apples everywhere!

title.jp: The Terror of Jyarei King Nyanma

synopsis: A Novel World has been darkened beyond any other, to the point where Kirinda can't even identify it. And yet, things seem deceptively simple once they get inside. What exactly's going on here? To make matters worse, Nyanma is cutting right to the chase and trying to assassinate Princess Aura in person!

There was something creeping under the surface of the latest Novel World, and it's finally revealed itself. The wolf's mecha takes off on its own, and proves itself to be a more powerful foe than the Eto Rangers have ever faced before.

There was already enough trades in this story, so when the Straw Millionaire just won't hold onto the straw that makes him a millionaire, he finds himself caught in the middle of a bidding war between the Eto Rangers and everyone else.

Peter Pan can't save Wendy if he can't even get to her, so when he develops a crippling fear of heights, things don't look good for her when she gets stuck on Captain Hook's airship. It's up to the Eto Rangers to talk some sense into him.

Bakumaru has to fight in a martial arts tournament for another girl's hand in order to save the Novel World, while Cream has to watch. It's about to get worse, too, when one of the competitors isn't interested in playing fair.

title.jp: Grandpa Aladdin and the Magic Lamp

synopsis: The Magic Lamp's been right under Aladdin's nose for sixty years in Edo-period Japan. But he still can't find it. He's not the only one who's been looking, though...

Yabba-dabba-do! The man in the story's a fierce, excitable hunter in the Stone Age, and he follows the law of the jungle, baby! That's bad news for the crane-turned-mammoth, though, because he's hungry and she's secretly his favorite food.

title.jp: The Weird, Weird House of Snacks

synopsis: Kirinda's carelessly-dropping-the-away-team-wherev­er has finally done it; he dropped them right on the witch, she's been knocked out cold, and the house of sweets is just a normal house right now. Looks like it's D.I.Y. time!

title.jp: Pray For Mercy From Puss in Boots

synopsis: Bakumaru's fear of cats is seriously getting to him. Which is especially bad now, because this proves to be the most dangerous Novel World yet.
Bakumaru will be a sitting duck against Nyanma and her elites in the state he's in right now. So, Gaoh comes up with a way to give him a little incentive.

The planet is going to be destroyed in five minutes. Only the legendary golden warrior can st- wait, wrong anime. Or is it? There's SOMETHING special about the Giraffe's Soul Stone, and the Eto Rangers are about to find out what it is.

Nyanma's not the only one who's flat-out embarrassed by Gousen's failure. The mischievous Jyuken wants to show that she doesn't need those other guys to kill the Eto Rangers, and in a world as bizarre as this, there's plenty of opportunities to find a few games to play with them.

Seems the roulette forgot someone this time; Bakumaru's not allowed in this Novel World. Someone has to be the leader, though, and Soufflé's desperate to prove that she's at least SLIGHTLY useful to the team...

This isn't your family film with singing fish. This is the Hans Christian Andersen version with a tragic ending, so when the Jyarei Cyborg threatens to make the world a happy one, the Eto Rangers have a difficult choice to make; let the world fall apart, or ruin everything.

For the first time ever, every Eto Ranger is allowed in the Novel World at once! But whoops. It's a trap, and now everyone but Bakumaru and Nyorori are wooden totems. They can deal with that later, though. There's gold everywhere! It's not like a bunch of pieces of wood are going anywhere... right?
